# Tiananmen Square Short — Meme-Maxxing Overhaul 

Following the strict integration of the `"Meme-Maxxing (Hyper-Density)"` rule in our documentation, the Tiananmen Square short has been violently rescripted into a 24-micro-scene masterclass of retention. Nothing loops more than twice and absolute meme density is maximized!

## Changes Made

- **Voiceover Redux (`scripts/generate-voiceover-tiananmen.ts`)**: Spliced the monologue into exactly 24 aggressive bursts of sarcastic Vietnamese narrative (averaging ~3.5 seconds each), pushing requests through ElevenLabs API for native timestamps.
- **Ultra Media Mapping (`scripts/copy-media-tiananmen.ts`)**: Swept your newly updated `memeDatabase` to harness 24 unique reaction assets perfectly correlating to script events (including nuclear blasts, fake news banners, cats staring, rich men splashing money, and chaotic offices).
- **Remotion Core Updates (`src/components/TiananmenSquareShort.tsx`)**: Re-coded the core video array to iterate securely over all 24 micro-scenes. Every 3.5 seconds, the entire layout punches in with a dynamic background glitch while the perfectly-synced glowing captions bounce forward.

